The paper deals with graph drawing algorithms, specifically extending a drawing of a subgraph to the entire graph using straight-line and polyline edges. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also introduces the concept of star complexity of a polygon, which is related to the complexity of the drawing, and discusses the worst-case complexity of the problem. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper mentions the complexity of testing whether a star-shaped inner face can be extended to a straight-line drawing, which could be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
